Remove the last element from an array.

Returns a new array with the last element removed.

```js
pop(array: [KclValue]): KclValue
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `array` | [`[KclValue]`](/docs/kcl/types/KclValue) | The array to pop from.  Must not be empty. | Yes |

### Returns

[`KclValue`](/docs/kcl/types/KclValue) - Any KCL value.


### Examples

```js
arr = [1, 2, 3, 4]
new_arr = pop(arr)
assert(
  new_arr[0],
  isEqualTo = 1,
  tolerance = 0.00001,
  error = "1 is the first element of the array",
)
assert(
  new_arr[1],
  isEqualTo = 2,
  tolerance = 0.00001,
  error = "2 is the second element of the array",
)
assert(
  new_arr[2],
  isEqualTo = 3,
  tolerance = 0.00001,
  error = "3 is the third element of the array",
)
```
